review_blob: A teaser for regular Yuengling lager. Few extra calories for the traditional lager is worth it to me.

Growing up a stones throw from this local brew, Yuengling was and still is a favorite Lager choice for me. Great overall balance, awesome smooth amber color, and goes down super smooth.  Feel bad people outside the North East have limited or no availability to this brew as its very local.  Awesome super super cold from the tap...to me tastes a bit differnt from the bottle so i would say let it breath a minute if you only have bottles.  No let down brew all around. Great product!

when im looking for a cheap, no let down beer game playing brew, BLL for me is decent choice.  You know what your getting...not much but a light fruity "beer". ...expecting much substance or anything else then sure to be let down....but take it for what it is and your golden.

really enjoyed this brew, strong aroma, imemdiately hit me with Blackberry flavor...not just a hint but a nice punch! A nice surprise after the overly pungent SA Cherry Wheat tasting.  BB Witbier  however seems more suited for a seasonal winter brew accompanying Oktoberfest, not sure why it was offered all summer long in local stores.
Overall not bad but a lacked in depth and flavor in my opinion.  Little aroma and substance however a nice light snack for the summer time...but not much more.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Overly bitter in my opinion and lacking in promised aroma.  Brought the hops for sure, but no flavor to back it up ...just in my opinion.

Aroma is what stands out on this brew mostly for me.  Hits you the second you let it breath away from the bottle.  The 120 IPA is said to be better when its poured out and let to breath a bit...I agree with the 60min IPA also. Overall an awesome Delaware brewed beer. Enjoyed the hoppiness very much.

Confused on why this brew is offered year round?...as it came across to me as like it was better suited along side OcktoberFest in the Winter time.  Strong pungent flavor of cherries which gets to be a little much after 1 or 2. Did not lack in flavor, however aftertaste was rough.  I love Sam Adams brews, but Cherry Wheat not my favorite.

Ive been a fan of BM for a while, only recently have I recognized the simplicity of this brew. Overall great taste...especially being an American brewed beer. Credit to Coors. brewing company to come up with a clever marketing strategy to distinguish this brew from the usual big 3 offerings.
